    "Body": " Consultancy - Writer, Office of Innovation, New York, 11.5 months UNICEF - 4.3 New York, NY Apply Now Job Details Temporary | ContractEstimated: $51,000 - $64,000 a year12 days ago Benefits Health Insurance Qualifications Writing Skills AI SharePoint Bachelor's Degree Master's Degree Full Job Description UNICEF works in some of the world\u2019s toughest places, to reach the world\u2019s most disadvantaged children. To save their lives. To defend their rights. To help them fulfill their potential. Across 190 countries and territories, we work for every child, everywhere, every day, to build a better world for everyone. And we never give up. For every child, innovate... UNICEF has a 70-year history of innovating for children. We believe that new approaches, partnerships, technologies and ways of financing are key to building a better world for children and young people. The Office of Innovation is a creative and agile global team. Worldwide, we innovate to tackle the most pressing problems faced by the most vulnerable children. We work with new technologies, new forms of partnerships, new ways of working and financing and new ways to find, nurture and share creative solutions for children and young people. How can you make a difference? You will produce leading content for a diverse set of external and internal audiences for our \u201cGIGA\u201d project, which aims to get every school on earth online; how we use innovative financing to bring change for children; and, how UNICEF\u2019s Office of Innovation nurtures innovation worldwide. Turning complex, technical information into clear, concise and compelling copy will be key to your role. You will work directly with the manager, innovative solutions, and the manager, innovative finance and in close coordination with the Office of Innovation communications team. GIGA GIGA, an initiative launched by UNICEF and ITU in September 2019, aims to connect every school to the internet and every young person to information, opportunity and choice. You will lead in generating high-quality content for external and internal audiences. You will lead on structuring and populating the official GIGA website and create and lead a multichannel content strategy. Working with the manager, innovative solutions, GIGA team and communications team, you will: Produce top-line content, including at least 4 impact stories, blogs or new webpages and supporting social media and internal communications posts each month. Produce and maintain a narrative and messaging document, with targeted messaging for all audiences identified by the GIGA team and communication team for use across all channels. Create, produce and oversee dissemination of a quarterly GIGA email newsletter. Create an online content strategy and revised information architecture for the GIGA website. Create press releases, guidance notes, FAQs, stories, interviews, blogs and opinion pieces around milestones and events, such as the World Economic Forum and UN General Assembly. As required, preparing briefing materials, articles, presentations, and other supporting documents to communicate complex and technical information in clear and simple language. Innovative Finance UNICEF defines innovative finance as any financing approach that helps to leverage additional resources for development through new financial structures, as well as making resources more efficient. You will lead in generating high-quality content for external and internal audiences. You will lead on creating and implementing a content-led communications strategy for innovative finance in line with the global innovative financing strategy. Internal communications will be important. Working with the manager, innovative finance (IF), the IF team and communications team, you will: Create and implement a content-led communications strategy for innovative finance. Produce and maintain a narrative and messaging document, with targeted messaging for all stakeholders and audiences identified by the IF team for use across all channels. Create 3 impact stories, blogs, new webpages each month for use across UNICEF\u2019s internal and external channels, including ICON, Sharepoint, Yammer and external websites and social feeds. Create, produce and oversee dissemination of a quarterly IF email newsletter. Create or edit press releases, FAQs, guidance notes, stories, interviews, presentations, blogs and opinion pieces for milestones and events, such as the UNICEF Executive Board Meeting. As required, prepare briefing materials, articles, presentations, and other supporting documents to communicate complex and technical information in clear and simple language. Innovation content creation Working with the Innovation communications team and the wider innovation team, you will: Assist in creating and editing new and existing content, including stories, blogs briefing notes and publications that communicate complex and technical information in clear language. Assist in creating compelling content across UNICEF\u2019s internal communications channels, to help build and grow a culture of innovation across the organisation. Advise and assist technical and scientific staff on how best explain complex information clearly. Assist in adding to the Office of Innovation communications strategy and content plan. About you You are a master storyteller with an eye for detail. You write with clarity, confidence and flair. Ideally, you\u2019ll bring proven experience in writing and editing across complex, technical subjects and creating content strategies in at least one of the following sectors; innovation, technology, finance, human rights or international development. You understand the importance of building strong working relationships. To qualify as an advocate for every child you will have\u2026 An advanced university degree (Master\u2019s or higher) in Communication, Journalism, Public Relations, Information or Telecommunications Technology or other relevant field. A first University Degree in a relevant field combined with 2 additional years of professional experience may be accepted in lieu of an Advanced University Degree. A minimum of 2 years of professional experience in a relevant field. Skilled wordsmith who can develop stories, how-to guides, FAQs and other content that communicates technical complexity with ease and clarity. A strong, proven track record of developing quality written content. Experience in creating communications strategies and content plans. Capacity to prioritize and manage a diverse range of partners, projects and activities. World class interpersonal skills. An understanding of the role technology plays in the development and humanitarian sectors, as well as the UN system. Familiarity with innovative finance tools, including for financing for development. Familiarity with emerging technology areas such as artificial intelligence, blockchain and digital connectivity. Experience working with digital and social media, preferably with a tech/innovation perspective Understanding of UNICEF Innovation operating environment and priority partners Ability to work with a diverse team in a rapidly-changing work environment and adapt to unforeseen changes Fluency in English is required. Competence in another UN language is an advantage. Visa requirement: With the exception of the US Citizens, G4 Visa and Green Card holders, should the selected candidate and his/her household members reside in the United States under a different visa, the consultant and his/her household members are required to change their visa status to G4, and the consultant's household members (spouse) will require an Employment Authorization Card (EAD) to be able to work, even if he/she was authorized to work under the visa held prior to switching to G-4. Payment details and further considerations Monthly payment, based on monthly tasks and progress reports, approved upon monthly review with supervisor. Consultant is responsible for his/her own health and travel insurance Consultant is eligible for standard DSA for all work-related travel For every Child, you demonstrate\u2026 UNICEF's values of Care, Respect, Integrity, Trust, and Accountability (CRITA) and core competencies in Communication, Working with People and Drive for Results. The functional competencies required for this post are... Learning and researching (I) Creating and innovating (I) Adapting and responding to change (I) View our competency framework at http://www.unicef.org/about/employ/files/UNICEF_Competencies.pdf UNICEF is committed to diversity and inclusion within its workforce, and encourages all candidates, irrespective of gender, nationality, religious and ethnic backgrounds, including persons living with disabilities, to apply to become a part of the organization. UNICEF has a zero-tolerance policy on conduct that is incompatible with the aims and objectives of the United Nations and UNICEF, including sexual exploitation and abuse, sexual harassment, abuse of authority and discrimination. UNICEF also adheres to strict child safeguarding principles. All selected candidates will be expected to adhere to these standards and principles and will therefore undergo rigorous reference and background checks. Background checks will include the verification of academic credential(s) and employment history. Selected candidates may be required to provide additional information to conduct a background check. Remarks: Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted and advance to the next stage of the selection process. Individuals engaged under a consultancy or individual contract will not be considered \u201cstaff members\u201d under the Staff Regulations and Rules of the United Nations and UNICEF\u2019s policies and procedures, and will not be entitled to benefits provided therein (such as leave entitlements and medical insurance coverage). Their conditions of service will be governed by their contract and the General Conditions of Contracts for the Services of Consultants and Individual Contractors. Consultants and individual contractors are responsible for determining their tax liabilities and for the payment of any taxes and/or duties, in accordance with local or other applicable laws. Opening Date Tue Jun 09 2020 08:00:00 GMT-0500 (Central Daylight Time) Eastern Daylight Time Closing Date Tue Jun 23 2020 22:55:00 GMT-0500 (Central Daylight Time) "
